### Animation Performance

#### Use Hardware-Accelerated Properties
- ‚úÖ **Transform over position**: GPU accelerated
- ‚úÖ **Opacity for fades**: Also GPU accelerated
- ‚úÖ **Avoid layout properties**: Don't animate width, height, top, left
- ‚úÖ **Use will-change sparingly**: Prepare for animations

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Hardware-accelerated animations */
.slide-in {
  transform: translateX(-100%);
  transition: transform 300ms ease-out;
}

.slide-in.active {
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.fade-in {
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 300ms ease-out;
}

.fade-in.active {
  opacity: 1;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Using will-change for complex animations */
.animated-element {
  will-change: transform;        /* Prepare browser for transform changes */
}

.animated-element.animating {
  animation: complex-animation 1s ease-in-out;
}

.animated-element.done {
  will-change: auto;             /* Remove after animation completes */
}

/* ‚ùå Bad: Animating layout properties (causes reflow) */
.bad-animation {
  transition: width 300ms, height 300ms, top 300ms, left 300ms;
}
```

#### Respect User Preferences
- ‚úÖ **Check prefers-reduced-motion**: Accessibility requirement
- ‚úÖ **Disable non-essential animations**: For users who prefer less motion
- ‚úÖ **Keep functional animations**: Essential feedback remains
- ‚úÖ **Reduce duration**: Make animations faster

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Respecting motion preferences */
.animated-card {
  transition: transform 300ms ease-out;
}

.animated-card:hover {
  transform: scale(1.05);
}

/* Reduce motion for users who prefer it */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .animated-card {
    transition: none;            /* Disable animation */
  }
  
  .animated-card:hover {
    transform: scale(1.02);      /* Subtle, instant feedback */
  }
}

/* Alternative: Faster animations instead of removing */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

#### 60 FPS Performance
- ‚úÖ **Target 60 fps**: 16.67ms per frame
- ‚úÖ **Use requestAnimationFrame**: For smooth animations
- ‚úÖ **Throttle/debounce**: Limit expensive operations
- ‚úÖ **Monitor performance**: Use DevTools Performance tab

```javascript
// ‚úÖ Good: Smooth scroll with requestAnimationFrame
function smoothScrollTo(target, duration = 1000) {
  const start = window.pageYOffset;
  const distance = target - start;
  let startTime = null;

  function animation(currentTime) {
    if (startTime === null) startTime = currentTime;
    const elapsed = currentTime - startTime;
    const progress = Math.min(elapsed / duration, 1);
    
    // Easing function
    const easeInOutCubic = progress < 0.5
      ? 4 * progress * progress * progress
      : 1 - Math.pow(-2 * progress + 2, 3) / 2;
    
    window.scrollTo(0, start + distance * easeInOutCubic);
    
    if (progress < 1) {
      requestAnimationFrame(animation);
    }
  }
  
  requestAnimationFrame(animation);
}

// ‚úÖ Good: Debounce expensive operations
function debounce(func, wait) {
  let timeout;
  return function executedFunction(...args) {
    const later = () => {
      clearTimeout(timeout);
      func(...args);
    };
    clearTimeout(timeout);
    timeout = setTimeout(later, wait);
  };
}

// Use debounce for resize events
const handleResize = debounce(() => {
  console.log('Window resized');
  // Expensive operation here
}, 250);

window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize);
```

### Resource Loading

#### Critical CSS
- ‚úÖ **Inline critical CSS**: Above-the-fold styles in `<head>`
- ‚úÖ **Defer non-critical CSS**: Load later or async
- ‚úÖ **Minimize inlined CSS**: Only truly critical styles
- ‚úÖ **Remove unused CSS**: Use tools to purge unused styles

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Inline critical CSS -->
<head>
  <style>
    /* Critical above-the-fold styles */
    body { margin: 0; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }
    .header { background: #0066cc; padding: 1rem; }
    .hero { min-height: 100vh; display: flex; align-items: center; }
  </style>
  
  <!-- Preload main stylesheet -->
  <link rel="preload" href="styles.css" as="style" onload="this.onload=null;this.rel='stylesheet'">
  <noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"></noscript>
</head>
```

#### JavaScript Optimization
- ‚úÖ **Defer non-critical JS**: Use `defer` attribute
- ‚úÖ **Async for independent scripts**: Use `async` when order doesn't matter
- ‚úÖ **Code splitting**: Load only needed code
- ‚úÖ **Tree shaking**: Remove unused code

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Proper script loading -->
<head>
  <!-- Critical scripts only -->
  <script>
    // Minimal critical inline JS (dark mode, etc.)
  </script>
</head>

<body>
  <!-- Content -->
  
  <!-- Non-critical scripts at end with defer -->
  <script src="main.js" defer></script>
  
  <!-- Independent analytics with async -->
  <script src="analytics.js" async></script>
</body>
```

