### Caching Strategies

#### Browser Caching
- ‚úÖ **Set appropriate cache headers**: Long cache for static assets
- ‚úÖ **Version/hash filenames**: Force cache invalidation when updated
- ‚úÖ **Cache API responses**: Use Service Workers
- ‚úÖ **localStorage for data**: Cache API responses client-side

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Versioned/hashed filenames -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.a4f8d2.css">
<script src="main.7e3b9c.js" defer></script>
<img src="logo.f3a7c1.png" alt="Logo">

<!-- Server sets cache headers for static assets -->
<!-- Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable -->
```

```javascript
// ‚úÖ Good: Cache API responses
async function fetchWithCache(url, cacheTime = 5 * 60 * 1000) {
  const cacheKey = `cache_${url}`;
  const cached = localStorage.getItem(cacheKey);
  
  if (cached) {
    const { data, timestamp } = JSON.parse(cached);
    
    // Return cached data if not expired
    if (Date.now() - timestamp < cacheTime) {
      return data;
    }
  }
  
  // Fetch fresh data
  const response = await fetch(url);
  const data = await response.json();
  
  // Cache the response
  localStorage.setItem(cacheKey, JSON.stringify({
    data,
    timestamp: Date.now()
  }));
  
  return data;
}
```

## ‚ùå DON'T (Anti-patterns)

### Loading Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Blank screens**: Don't show nothing while loading
- ‚ùå **No feedback**: Don't leave users wondering if something is happening
- ‚ùå **Synchronous operations**: Don't block UI with long operations
- ‚ùå **No error states**: Don't ignore failed loads

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: No loading state -->
<div id="content">
  <!-- Nothing until data loads -->
</div>

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Loading state with skeleton -->
<div id="content">
  <div class="skeleton" aria-busy="true">
    Loading content...
  </div>
</div>
```

### Image Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Large unoptimized images**: Don't serve full-res images
- ‚ùå **No dimensions**: Don't omit width/height (causes layout shift)
- ‚ùå **All eager loading**: Don't load all images immediately
- ‚ùå **Single format**: Don't ignore modern formats (WebP, AVIF)

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Unoptimized image without dimensions -->
<img src="huge-image-4k.jpg" alt="Image">

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Optimized responsive image with dimensions -->
<picture>
  <source srcset="image.avif" type="image/avif">
  <source srcset="image.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img 
    src="image.jpg" 
    alt="Image"
    loading="lazy"
    width="800"
    height="600">
</picture>
```

### Animation Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Animating expensive properties**: Don't animate width, height, top, left
- ‚ùå **Ignoring reduced motion**: Don't ignore accessibility preferences
- ‚ùå **Too many animations**: Don't animate everything
- ‚ùå **Blocking animations**: Don't prevent user interaction

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Animating layout properties */
.bad {
  transition: width 300ms, height 300ms, left 300ms, top 300ms;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Hardware-accelerated properties */
.good {
  transition: transform 300ms, opacity 300ms;
}

/* ‚ùå Bad: Ignoring motion preferences */
.animated {
  animation: spin 2s infinite;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Respecting motion preferences */
.animated {
  animation: spin 2s infinite;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .animated {
    animation: none;
  }
}
```

### Resource Loading Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Blocking resources**: Don't block render with large JS
- ‚ùå **No code splitting**: Don't load entire app upfront
- ‚ùå **Render-blocking CSS**: Don't block with non-critical CSS
- ‚ùå **No compression**: Don't serve uncompressed assets

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Render-blocking script in head -->
<head>
  <script src="huge-bundle.js"></script>
</head>

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Deferred, split bundles -->
