## üìä Performance Metrics

| Metric | Good | Needs Improvement | Poor |
|--------|------|-------------------|------|
| **First Contentful Paint (FCP)** | < 1.8s | 1.8s - 3s | > 3s |
| **Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)** | < 2.5s | 2.5s - 4s | > 4s |
| **Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)** | < 0.1 | 0.1 - 0.25 | > 0.25 |
| **First Input Delay (FID)** | < 100ms | 100ms - 300ms | > 300ms |
| **Time to Interactive (TTI)** | < 3.8s | 3.8s - 7.3s | > 7.3s |
| **Total Blocking Time (TBT)** | < 200ms | 200ms - 600ms | > 600ms |

## üìù Key Points

### Must Have
- Loading indicators for all async operations
- Skeleton screens for content loading
- Image optimization (dimensions, lazy loading, modern formats)
- Hardware-accelerated animations only
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Resource optimization (defer, async, preload)

### Do
- Show immediate feedback (optimistic UI)
- Use skeleton screens and loading states
- Lazy load below-the-fold images
- Use WebP/AVIF with JPEG/PNG fallbacks
- Animate transform and opacity only
- Inline critical CSS
- Defer non-critical JavaScript
- Set cache headers appropriately
- Monitor Core Web Vitals

### Don't
- Don't show blank screens while loading
- Don't load all images eagerly
- Don't animate width, height, top, left
- Don't ignore reduced motion preferences
- Don't block rendering with large bundles
- Don't forget image dimensions (causes layout shift)
- Don't ignore caching strategies
- Don't skip performance testing

